{"key":"post-8981729","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8981729</id>\n<content>If you insist on running a fan in a terrarium, run it for no more than ten seconds or so.&amp;nbsp; Otherwise, you'll dry out the surface of your substrate, impeding fruiting.&amp;nbsp; I suggest no fans at all.&amp;nbsp; If you're growing cubes, you don't need to fan a shotgun terrarium.&amp;nbsp; I recommend it, but many growers skip that part.&amp;nbsp; If you're growing oysters, you'll need to fan in addition to all the holes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8982207</next>\n<prev>8981429</prev>\n<first>8976125</first>\n<last>8984344</last>\n<when>1222318888</when>\n<utime>09/25/08 08:01 AM</utime>\n</post>"}